The paper deals with a coverage extension scheme for the downlink of massive MIMO systems, which involves the use of precoding matrices consisting of orthogonal vectors. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also derives analytical expressions for the downlink coverage probability, which involves system-level analysis and optimization, and hence could be categorized under systems and control (cs.SY). The use of multiple antennas and antenna selection also suggests a connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and communication networks (cs.COM).
